-- Lily Safra Donates Gerhard Richter Painting to Israel Museum
-- B y   C a l e v   B e n - D a v i d
-- 2012-01-15T09:11:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/lily-safra-donates-gerhard-richter-painting-to-israel-museum.html
Lily Safra, widow of Brazilian
banker Edmond Safra, has donated  Gerhard Richter ’s painting
“Abstraktes Bild 849-3 (1997)” to the Israel Museum, the
Jerusalem-based institution said today in an e-mailed statement.  The Richter painting was purchased for $20.8 million at a
 Sotheby’s (BID)  auction in November.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Calev Ben-David in Jerusalem at 
 cbendavid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alisa Odenheimer at 
 aodenheimer@bloomberg.net  